	painsHeading="What pains India"
	painsIntroHtml={`Behind the festivals and the fast-growing economy, ordinary families carry heavy burdens. The data tells a sobering story &mdash; and it is into exactly these aches that the Father&rsquo;s heart speaks.`}
	painStats={[
		{ value: '~203 million', label: 'people still live in multidimensional poverty (health, schooling, basic necessities)' },
		{ value: '170,746', label: 'lives lost to suicide in 2024 — about one every three minutes' },
		{ value: '33.5%', label: 'of those suicides were driven by family problems — the leading cause' },
		{ value: '34.7%', label: 'of households still lack clean cooking fuel; 1 in 4 lack proper sanitation' },
		{ value: '7.6%', label: 'of suicides were linked to drug or alcohol addiction' },
		{ value: '10,546', label: 'farmers and farm laborers died by suicide — debt a major driver' },
		{ value: '~30 million', label: 'orphaned children — the largest of any nation, ~15–20% of all orphans on earth; ~3.4M lost a caregiver to COVID' },
	]}
	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Daily-wage earners make up the largest share of those lost to suicide &mdash; the people working hardest simply to survive. Debt drives farmers to despair; addiction fractures homes; and family breakdown, now the number-one cause of suicide, reaches into marriages and across generations. Divorce, long among the world&rsquo;s lowest, is climbing sharply in India&rsquo;s cities.</p><p>These are not abstract numbers. They are fathers without work, mothers without rest, sons and daughters without hope. India does not need another distant authority to obey &mdash; it needs a Father who draws near.</p>`}
	painsSources={[
		{ label: 'UNDP/NITI Aayog MPI 2024', url: 'https://hdr.undp.org/sites/default/files/Country-Profiles/MPI2024/IND.pdf' },
		{ label: 'NCRB 2024 (suicide data)', url: 'https://theprint.in/india/family-problems-leading-cause-of-suicide-in-india-highest-in-18-30-age-bracket-ncrb/2925220/' },
		{ label: 'Orphans in India (Borgen Project)', url: 'https://borgenproject.org/orphans-in-india/' },
	]}
	faithsHeading="What “our Father” offers India"
	faithsIntroHtml={`India is home to Hindus, Muslims, Buddhists, Sikhs, Jains, and millions seeking. The Father&rsquo;s Heart Bible&trade; does not erase that search &mdash; it answers the longing underneath it. For the first time in English, Scripture reveals God not as a remote deity to appease, but as a <em>Father</em> who runs to meet His children.`}
	faithsBlocks={[
		{ heading: 'For the one seeking intimacy', bodyHtml: `Many faiths reach toward the divine through ritual and distance. The Father&rsquo;s Heart Bible&trade; reveals a God who reaches first &mdash; <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/john/3" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">&ldquo;our Father so loved the world&rdquo;</a> &mdash; offering not a transaction but a relationship, closeness instead of fear.` },
		{ heading: 'For the one longing to belong', bodyHtml: `In a land of caste, class, and a billion striving souls, the Father calls every person &mdash; rich or poor, high or low &mdash; His beloved son or daughter. Belonging is no longer earned; it is given.` },
		{ heading: 'For the one carrying shame or debt', bodyHtml: `To the farmer crushed by debt and the family broken by addiction, the Father offers a home with no ledger of wrongs &mdash; the relief of being received, not judged.` },
		{ heading: 'For the one without hope', bodyHtml: `Where despair drives so many to the edge, the Father speaks <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/jeremiah/29" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">a future and a hope</a> &mdash; identity, intimacy, and inheritance that no circumstance can take away.` },
		{ heading: 'For the orphan and the fatherless', bodyHtml: `India holds the largest number of orphaned children on earth, and COVID left millions more without a parent. To every one of them Scripture makes a promise: <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/psalms/68" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">&ldquo;A father to the fatherless&hellip; is God in his holy dwelling.&rdquo;</a> Our Father runs to the child no one came back for.` },
	]}
	whyHeading="Why the Father's Heart Bible™ for India"
	whyBlocks={[
		{ heading: 'God revealed as Father, not a distant deity', bodyHtml: `In a culture rich with names and images for the divine, the Father&rsquo;s Heart Bible&trade; offers something no English Bible has before: it reveals God as <em>Father</em> wherever Scripture reveals Him that way &mdash; from <a href=\"https://fathersheartbible.com/read/genesis/1\" style=\"color: var(--color-brand);\" class=\"hover:underline\">Genesis 1:1</a> onward. Not a remote power to appease, but a Father who loves His sons and daughters.` },
		{ heading: 'Free, with audio, on any phone', bodyHtml: `No purchase, no app, no sign-up. The whole Bible is free to <a href=\"https://fathersheartbible.com/read\" style=\"color: var(--color-brand);\" class=\"hover:underline\">read online</a> with audio on every chapter &mdash; built to work on a basic smartphone, which is how most of India reads the internet.` },
		{ heading: 'A starting point for every reader', bodyHtml: `New to the Bible? Our <a href=\"/guides/where-to-start-reading-the-bible/\" style=\"color: var(--color-brand);\" class=\"hover:underline\">where-to-start guide</a> and <a href=\"/guides/how-to-read-the-bible/\" style=\"color: var(--color-brand);\" class=\"hover:underline\">how-to-read-the-Bible guide</a> walk you through the first steps, so you&rsquo;re never lost on page one.` },
